First, we need to find the Cartesian product A × B. The Cartesian product of two sets A and B, denoted A × B, is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is in A and b is in B.

A × B = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4)}

Now, we need to find the union of the set A × B with the set {1}. The union of two sets A and B, denoted A ∪ B, is the set of all elements that are in A, in B, or in both.

(A × B) ∪ {1} = {(1, 3), (1, 4), (2, 3), (2, 4), 1}
